    {
      "text": "Olympic Summer Games is an official video game of the Atlanta 1996 Olympic Games. It is the successor to Olympic Gold and Winter Olympics. It was the last \"Olympic\" video game released for the fourth generation of consoles, as well as the Game Boy.\nIt follows the already common button mashing techniques of previous (and future) games, with the usual exceptions.\nIt has 10 events (three more than Olympic Gold), with all but two based on track and field events. Unlike Winter Olympics, there are no major differences between each event on different platforms.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "Olympic Summer Games: Atlanta 1996 est un jeu vidéo de sport et fonctionne sur Mega Drive, Super Nintendo, 3DO, PlayStation, Game Boy et Windows.",
